1- select the specific column
2- filter row
3- combine multiple condition

1- squares brackets
2- boolean conditions

selecting column
1-a = series
2- dataframe multiple column of data

column = df["column name"]
subset = df["column1","column2","..."]

filtering rows
boolean indexing

# based on a single condition
filtered_rows = df[df["salary"]>29999]

combine the multiple condition
filtered_rows = df[df["salary"]>29999] & df[df["age"]>17]